  <prompt>Configure the existing AssociationResolver PCF control on the sprk_communication model-driven form. The control must be bound to the sprk_regardingrecordtype lookup field and configured to resolve across all 8 supported entity types, populating denormalized regarding fields automatically.</prompt>

  <role>SPAARKE platform developer expert in PCF control configuration, Dataverse form customization, and polymorphic association patterns</role>

  <goal>AssociationResolver PCF is properly placed and configured on the sprk_communication form, bound to sprk_regardingrecordtype, with entity-specific lookup fields configured for all 8 entity types. Denormalized fields auto-populate when an entity is selected.</goal>

  <context>
    <background>The AssociationResolver PCF control is a production-ready component that handles polymorphic entity resolution. It allows users to first select an entity type (Matter, Project, Invoice, etc.) and then search for a specific record of that type. When a record is selected, it populates the sprk_regardingrecordtype lookup and the appropriate denormalized regarding fields (sprk_regardingmatter, sprk_regardingproject, etc.). The control reads its entity configuration from the sprk_recordtype_ref entity.</background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/client/pcf/AssociationResolver/AssociationResolverApp.tsx</file>
      <file>src/client/pcf/AssociationResolver/RecordSelectionHandler.ts</file>
      <file>.claude/patterns/dataverse/polymorphic-resolver.md</file>
      <file>docs/data-model/sprk_communication-data-schema.md</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-006">Use PCF control (AssociationResolver), not legacy webresources.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-022">PCF uses React 16 APIs only; unmanaged solutions only.</constraint>
    <constraint source="Dataverse Schema">Regarding fields: sprk_regardingorganization (not account), sprk_regardingperson (not contact).</constraint>
    <constraint source="Dataverse Schema">8 entity types: Matter, Project, Invoice, Analysis, Organization, Person, Work Assignment, Budget.</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file path=".claude/patterns/dataverse/polymorphic-resolver.md" reason="AssociationResolver configuration pattern"/>
      <file path="docs/data-model/sprk_communication-data-schema.md" reason="Entity field names for regarding lookups"/>
    </files>
  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step order="1">Read .claude/patterns/dataverse/polymorphic-resolver.md to understand AssociationResolver configuration requirements.</step>
    <step order="2">Read AssociationResolverApp.tsx and RecordSelectionHandler.ts to understand the control's input properties and binding requirements.</step>
    <step order="3">Document placement of AssociationResolver PCF control on the communication form's Association section, bound to sprk_regardingrecordtype lookup field.</step>
    <step order="4">Configure entity-specific lookup fields for all 8 entity types: sprk_regardingmatter (sprk_matter), sprk_regardingproject (sprk_project), sprk_regardinginvoice (sprk_invoice), sprk_regardinganalysis (sprk_analysis), sprk_regardingorganization (sprk_organization), sprk_regardingperson (sprk_person), sprk_regardingworkassignment (sprk_workassignment), sprk_regardingbudget (sprk_budget).</step>
    <step order="5">Verify sprk_recordtype_ref entity has configuration rows for all 8 entity types that the control will query.</step>
    <step order="6">Document the control property bindings: bound field, entity type list, denormalized field mappings.</step>
    <step order="7">Verify control loads with correct entity configs from sprk_recordtype_ref and denormalized fields auto-populate on record selection.</step>
  </steps>

